reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewText: In terms of durability, the Supershieldz Tempered Glass Screen Protector has proven its resilience over time. It has effectively shielded my phone from daily wear and tear, including accidental drops and encounters with keys or other items in my pocket. The tempered glass maintains its integrity, preventing any cracks or chips from compromising the screen underneath. This durability has saved me the hassle and expense of potential screen replacements, making it a cost-effective investment for the longevity of my device.Another notable feature is the easy maintenance of this screen protector. Cleaning is a breeze, and the oleophobic coating ensures that smudges and fingerprints are effortlessly wiped away with a quick swipe. This not only keeps my phone looking pristine at all times but also contributes to a consistently clear and vibrant display. The maintenance simplicity further enhances the overall satisfaction I've experienced with the Supershieldz screen protector.In conclusion, the Supershieldz Samsung Galaxy S20 FE 5G Tempered Glass Screen Protector has exceeded my expectations in terms of installation ease, durability, and maintenance. It provides robust protection without compromising the clarity and touch sensitivity of the device. If you're seeking a reliable screen protector that combines functionality with quality craftsmanship, the Supershieldz Tempered Glass Screen Protector is an excellent choice for safeguarding your Samsung Galaxy S20 FE 5G.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Easy to apply
reviews.reviewText: It was easy to apply the screen protector. Stays in place well. The way my phone screen is rounded is the biggest issue. If they could find a way to bring the edges out further or round them out would be five stars. I did drop the 1st phone once and it cracked all the way across, beyond repair. So I feel that the protector could benefit from being thicker. All in all pretty good quality.

reviews.reviewText: This is a great protector and it has the best/easiest application method of all the ones I've tried over the years. Unfortunately, I did not read "FE" so it doesn't fit my regular S20.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Dropped my phone on tile- it did it's job!
reviews.reviewText: Awesome screen protector! I typically don't use one, but since I was getting a new device I said well, this time maybe it's a good idea, just to be safe. Sure enough, a month or so after putting the protector on I dropped my phone HARD on hotel floor tile. I just knew my phone was done for. To my surprise, when I picked it up, only the corners of the screen protector were broken, and honestly, they weren't all that bad. Removing it and replacing it was a piece of cake too! Definitely a good brand, significantly better than expected!

I usually purchase Spigen screen protectors which I consider to be one of the highest quality products out there. After finding out that Spigen did not make a glass screen protector for the S20 FE 5G, I took a chance on this product from Supershieldz. I'm glad I did. This screen protector checks all the boxes, relatively inexpensive, easy to install, excellent touch sensitivity, oleo and hydrophobic coated, 2.5D rounded edges, and excellent overall fit. Highly recommended.
Have not installed on phone yet ,but I can tell by other products this is worth the money you pay,

The old plastic screen protector that my phone had was starting to look pretty ratty. Decided to go with a glass one this time. Was not disappointed. Liked the whole sticker-Hinge installation method. Despite being simplistic it actually worked perfectly. Fingerprint reading still works perfect. Screen Actually seems more touch sensitive vs the plastic screen protector. Love that it came with 3 WHOLE installation kits so I can replace it a few times. Breathed some new life into my phone.
